commit.message: Derived.TypeSynonyms: Ensure orphan instances are in scope
TextShow.Data.Typeable: Handle partial tuple applications correctly

Use extended literals syntax for TH-generated TextShow instances

This requires bumping the lower version bounds on `deriving-compat` to ensure
that similar changes are present when generating `Show(1)(2)` instances with
the TH machinery in `Text.Show.Deriving`.

Fixes #61.
Use mkNameG_fld where needed on GHC 9.8+

Mention text-show-instances in documentation

Inspired by a comment from
https://github.com/RyanGlScott/text-show/issues/62#issuecomment-1664230660.

Support building with QuickCheck-2.14.3

Prompted by commercialhaskell/stackage#6995
Avoid liftA2-related import warning in GHC 9.6
Bump upper version bounds for GHC 9.6
Add TextShow instances for SomeChar and S{Nat,Symbol,Char}

Adapt to Solo data constructor becoming MkSolo in `ghc-prim-0.10.0`

Fixes #59.
Fix for old versions of GHC
